The Nairobi Metropolitan Services (NMS) is set to refurbish the iconic City Square Post Office footbridge along the busy Haile Selassie Avenue even as plans to construct a new one remain in the pipeline.
This is after the footbridge was damaged by a trailer carrying an excavator earlier in December 2020.



