Part of the upgrade will see NMS erect a temporary steel structure to support the bridge as plans to construct a new one get underway.
In the meantime, pedestrians and motorists have been advised to exercise caution. 










NMS Director of Transport and Public Works Engineer Michael Ochieng.
Photo credit: Collins Omulo | Nation Media Group


Temporary structure 
NMS Director of Roads, Infrastructure and Public Works Engineer Michael Ochieng said the temporary structure will be erected to support the footbridge in the short term as plans for the construction of a new footbridge are finalised.
He pointed out that zebra crossing signs have already been placed along the road for pedestrians' use, a situation that will temporarily slow down traffic flow along the busy avenue.



